<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<task id="035" project="jps-server-rollout">
  <metadata>
    <title>Convert DocumentClassifierHandler to thin JPS consumer preserving RAG logic</title>
    <phase>4</phase>
    <tags>bff-api, refactor</tags>
    <estimate>3h</estimate>
    <dependencies>014, 022</dependencies>
    <parallel-group>thin-wrapper</parallel-group>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    <goal>Convert DocumentClassifierHandler to a thin wrapper that routes through GenericAnalysisHandler while preserving its RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) example retrieval logic. If context.ActionSystemPrompt is JPS format, call PromptSchemaRenderer.Render() with injected RAG examples. Fallback to legacy prompt if not JPS.</goal>
    <context>
      DocumentClassifierHandler (Services/Ai/Tools/DocumentClassifierHandler.cs) differs from simple prompt-only handlers: it retrieves RAG examples from knowledge sources and injects them into the prompt.
      Rather than consolidate away all custom logic, this task converts it to a thin wrapper:
      1. Keep the handler class and RAG example retrieval
      2. Detect if context.ActionSystemPrompt is JPS format
      3. If JPS: call PromptSchemaRenderer.Render() with RAG examples injected as template parameters
      4. If legacy prompt: use old code path (fallback)

      This preserves the value of RAG augmentation while enabling JPS standardization.
    </context>
    <constraints>
      - Keep DocumentClassifierHandler class and DI registration
      - Preserve RAG example retrieval logic (do not remove)
      - Implement dual-path logic: JPS path (new) and legacy path (fallback)
      - Inject RAG examples as template parameters into JPS rendering
      - Maintain backward compatibility with existing legacy prompts
      - Follow .claude/patterns/ai/analysis-scopes.md for JPS structure
      - Follow ADR-010 (DI minimalism) — no new services
    </constraints>
  </prompt>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/api.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ai/analysis-scopes.md</file>
      <file>projects/jps-server-rollout/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read DocumentClassifierHandler.cs to understand RAG example retrieval and current prompt building logic</step>
    <step order="2">Identify where examples are injected into the prompt (typically in Render() method)</step>
    <step order="3">Implement dual-path logic in the handler:
      - Check if context.ActionSystemPrompt is JPS format (use existing IsJpsFormat() helper or create one)
      - If JPS: retrieve RAG examples, add to template parameters, call PromptSchemaRenderer.Render()
      - If legacy: use existing prompt building code
    </step>
    <step order="4">Extract RAG example retrieval into a separate helper method if not already isolated</step>
    <step order="5">Create test cases for both JPS and legacy paths with RAG examples</step>
    <step order="6">Build the project: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`</step>
    <step order="7">Run tests including DocumentClassifierHandler tests: `dotnet test src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "*DocumentClassifier*"`</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read</tool>
    <tool>Edit</tool>
    <tool>Bash(dotnet build)</tool>
    <tool>Bash(dotnet test)</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Tools/DocumentClassifierHandler.cs</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>DocumentClassifierHandler kept as thin wrapper</criterion>
    <criterion>RAG example retrieval logic preserved</criterion>
    <criterion>Dual-path logic implemented: JPS and legacy fallback</criterion>
    <criterion>RAG examples injected as template parameters in JPS path</criterion>
    <criterion>JPS path calls PromptSchemaRenderer.Render()</criterion>
    <criterion>Legacy path uses original prompt building code</criterion>
    <criterion>Test cases cover both paths with examples</criterion>
    <criterion>Project builds successfully</criterion>
    <criterion>All tests pass (including backward compatibility)</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
